President Trump addressed a group at the White House Mental Health Summit, expressing his commitment to helping Americans suffering from mental illness. He highlighted the decline in mental hospital beds and the lack of mental health services for millions of Americans. The President also emphasized the need for new institutions and the importance of keeping dangerous individuals off the streets. He mentioned the funding bill that provides $3.9 billion for mental health programs and discussed efforts to address the opioid epidemic and provide mental health screening for veterans. President Trump thanked the attendees for their work and acknowledged the challenges they face in their profession.